Text: This week started with our client meeting on Monday.
We met with Milair as well as 3 other SDHB staff members who had a stake in the project.

Through our discussions we were able to find out extra information that we hadn't yet acquired that were fairly important in the design of our application and database, such as doctors being able to be apart of more than 1 team.
We also suggested that with our limited time left on the project that we need to prioritize with what they think will be most vital since there are a lot of "nice to have" features.
Milair emailed us back later in the week with the list of features she thought were the most essential.
Overall from the meeting Milair and the others SDHB staff were happy with the progress and direction we are headed in and are very excited about how this will help them.
As for the work done over the week, we've continued to refine the UI and adapt the ERD with the newly acquired information.
I've updated and written MySQL scripts to create the database, and using the website Mockaroo was able to create dummy data to fill up all of the tables.
The dummy data isn't quite perfect but it will do the job for testing with.

We have been able to connect the application to the database and pull the data out from it, and we are working on the MVVM method of binding data to UI elements which is proving to be a steep learning curve.
I attempted to move the database onto AWS but ran into issues with the settings and wasn't able to access the database I was trying to create in there.
Roro had a go and was successfully able to create one so we now have the database online filled with dummy data and ready for testing.

The goals for the upcoming week will be to continue fleshing out the application and it's UI and to start trying to implement the functions that will complete the user stories now that we have the ground work in place.
